reviews: The product was good but it wasn't for me me. Their customer service however was very good and they gave me a full refund when I explained I didn't like it.

Order a size up for sure.
In my other Carhartts I'm a 32 and I had to order a 34 waist. Other than that they are great pants.
Will buy another one if my dogs ever destroy this thing. It's definitely their favourite toy to fight over.
Very comfortable and feel super durable however they fit small. I'm a 32 in Carhartt Ripstop pants and I had to order a 34 in these guys.
Super soft and feel very durable so far after a few washes.
Like the classic Klein handle for a terminal driver. Same Klein quality.

review_title: Worth a shot if you're thinking about it
reviews: Only had these for a few weeks but man they're sweet. Already cut through things my old Kleins never could.
Great quality. Fits a little snug though compared to my black Carhartt hat
Fits nicely in my Ford Focus. Came sooner than expected.
Exactly what I was looking for, however I needed to purchase a boot retainer for my Ford Focus.
I feel like these are better than the original Oral B bristle that came with my brush. And you get a lot for your money!
Great leashes for the money. They've held up well on my daily walks plus obedience training with two dogs.
Good glasses, they look dark from the outside but when you're wearing them it is actually quite comfortable if you're inside, and it blocks the sun if you're outside. Win-win
So far so good! I've been using then to store material in for work, like screws and such. Haven't had any holes or zipper issues.

I really like these pants but God damn, they don't last very long compared to my other Carhartts. The crotch always seems to get a hole in it after around 6 months of use. And that's alternating between 2 pairs of these suckers during the week.

They're good but I've noticed some holes forming and I've only had them for 6 months. My last set of work socks- fruit of the loom from Wal Mart- lasted almost 2 years and we're still intact. They're good work socks, just wish they were more durable.
Fit great and are comfy for working out. The stitching is a little flimsy on the bottom of the seams, as mine tore a little bit after one week.
Might be a little snug, but if you're wearing them to work out then that's some good motivation! Other than that they are great for the price.
